3303.definition: [μέν] a primary particle; properly, indicative of affirmation or concession (in fact); usually followed by a contrasted clause with {{G1161}} (this one, the former, etc.) Often compounded with other particles in an intensive or asseverative sense.

3304.definition: [μενοῦνγε] from {{G3303}} and {{G3767}} and {{G1065}}; so then at least

3305.definition: [μέντοι] from {{G3303}} and {{G5104}}; indeed though, i.e. however

3306.definition: [μένω] a primary verb; to stay (in a given place, state, relation or expectancy)

3307.definition: [μερίζω] from {{G3313}}; to part, i.e. (literally) to apportion, bestow, share, or (figuratively) to disunite, differ

3308.definition: [μέριμνα] from {{G3307}} (through the idea of distraction); solicitude

3310.definition: [μερίς] feminine of {{G3313}}; a portion, i.e. province, share or (abstractly) participation

3313.definition: [μέρος] from an obsolete but more primary form of μείρομαι (to get as a section or allotment); a division or share (literally or figuratively, in a wide application)

3314.definition: [μεσημβρία] from {{G3319}} and {{G2250}}; midday; by implication, the south

3315.definition: [μεσιτεύω] from {{G3316}}; to interpose (as arbiter), i.e (by implication) to ratify (as surety)

3316.definition: [μεσίτης] from {{G3319}}; a go-between, i.e. (simply) an internunciator, or (by implication) a reconciler (intercessor)

3317.definition: [μεσονύκτιον] neuter of compound of {{G3319}} and {{G3571}}; midnight (especially as a watch)

3318.definition: [Μεσοποταμία] from {{G3319}} and {{G4215}}; Mesopotamia (as lying between the Euphrates and the Tigris; compare {{H763}}), a region of Asia

3319.definition: [μέσος] from {{G3326}}; middle (as an adjective or (neuter) noun)

3321.definition: [μεσουράνημα] from a presumed compound of {{G3319}} and {{G3772}}; mid-sky

3322.definition: [μεσόω] from {{G3319}}; to form the middle, i.e. (in point of time), to be half-way over

3323.definition: [Μεσσίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H4899}}); the Messias (i.e. Mashiach), or Christ

3324.definition: [μεστός] of uncertain derivation; replete (literally or figuratively)

3325.definition: [μεστόω] from {{G3324}}; to replenish, i.e. (by implication) to intoxicate

3326.definition: [μετά] a primary preposition (often used adverbially); properly, denoting accompaniment; "amid" (local or causal); modified variously according to the case (genitive association, or accusative succession) with which it is joined; occupying an intermediate position between {{G575}} or {{G1537}} and {{G1519}} or {{G4314}}; less intimate than {{G1722}} and less close than {{G4862}}) Often used in composition, in substantially the same relations of participation or proximity, and transfer or sequence.

3327.definition: [μεταβαίνω] from {{G3326}} and the base of {{G939}}; to change place

3328.definition: [μεταβάλλω] from {{G3326}} and {{G906}}; to throw over, i.e. (middle voice figuratively) to turn about in opinion

3329.definition: [μετάγω] from {{G3326}} and {{G718}}; to lead over, i.e. transfer (direct)

3330.definition: [μεταδίδωμι] from {{G3326}} and {{G1325}}; to give over, i.e. share

3331.definition: [μετάθεσις] from {{G3346}}; transposition, i.e. transferral (to heaven), disestablishment (of a law)

3332.definition: [μεταίρω] from {{G3326}} and {{G142}}; to betake oneself, i.e. remove (locally)

3333.definition: [μετακαλέω] from {{G3326}} and {{G2564}}; to call elsewhere, i.e. summon

3334.definition: [μετακινέω] from {{G3326}} and {{G2795}}; to stir to a place elsewhere, i.e. remove (figuratively)

3335.definition: [μεταλαμβάνω] from {{G3326}} and {{G2983}}; to participate; genitive case, to accept (and use)

3338.definition: [μεταμέλλομαι] from {{G3326}} and the middle voice of {{G3199}}; to care afterwards, i.e. regret

3339.definition: [μεταμορφόω] from {{G3326}} and {{G3445}}; to transform (literally or figuratively, "metamorphose")

3340.definition: [μετανοέω] from {{G3326}} and {{G3539}}; to think differently or afterwards, i.e. reconsider (morally, feel compunction)

3341.definition: [μετάνοια] from {{G3340}}; (subjectively) compunction (for guilt, including reformation); by implication, reversal (of (another's) decision)

3342.definition: [μεταξύ] from {{G3326}} and a form of {{G4862}}; betwixt (of place or person); (of time) as adjective, intervening, or (by implication) adjoining

3343.definition: [μεταπέμπω] from {{G3326}} and {{G3992}}; to send from elsewhere, i.e. (middle voice) to summon or invite

3344.definition: [μεταστρέφω] from {{G3326}} and {{G4762}}; to turn across, i.e. transmute or (figuratively) corrupt

3345.definition: [μετασχηματίζω] from {{G3326}} and a derivative of {{G4976}}; to transfigure or disguise; figuratively, to apply (by accommodation)

3346.definition: [μετατίθημι] from {{G3326}} and {{G5087}}; to transfer, i.e. (literally) transport, (by implication) exchange, (reflexively) change sides, or (figuratively) pervert

3348.definition: [μετέχω] from {{G3326}} and {{G2192}}; to share or participate; by implication, belong to, eat (or drink)

3349.definition: [μετεωρίζω] from a compound of {{G3326}} and a collateral form of {{G142}} or perhaps rather {{G109}} (compare "meteor"); to raise in mid-air, i.e. (figuratively) suspend (passively, fluctuate or be anxious)

3350.definition: [μετοικεσία] from a derivative of a compound of {{G3326}} and {{G3624}}; a change of abode, i.e. (specially), expatriation

3351.definition: [μετοικίζω] from the same as {{G3350}}; to transfer as a settler or captive, i.e colonize or exile

3353.definition: [μέτοχος] from {{G3348}}; participant, i.e. (as noun) a sharer; by implication, an associate

3354.definition: [μετρέω] from {{G3358}}; to measure (i.e. ascertain in size by a fixed standard); by implication, to admeasure (i.e. allot by rule)

3355.definition: [μετρητής] from {{G3354}}; a measurer, i.e. (specially), a certain standard measure of capacity for liquids

3356.definition: [μετριοπαθέω] from a compound of the base of {{G3357}} and {{G3806}}; to be moderate in passion, i.e. gentle (to treat indulgently)

3357.definition: [μετρίως] adverb from a derivative of {{G3358}}; moderately, i.e. slightly

3358.definition: [μέτρον] an apparently primary word; a measure ("metre"), literally or figuratively; by implication, a limited portion (degree)

3359.definition: [μέτωπον] from {{G3326}} and ops (the face); the forehead (as opposite the countenance)

3360.definition: [μέχρι]   or μεχρίςfrom {{G3372}}; as far as, i.e. up to a certain point (as a preposition, of extent (denoting the terminus, whereas {{G891}} refers especially to the space of time or place intervening) or conjunction)

3361.definition: [μή] a primary particle of qualified negation (whereas {{G3756}} expresses an absolute denial); (adverb) not, (conjunction) lest; also (as an interrogative implying a negative answer (whereas {{G3756}} expects an affirmative one)) whether Often used in compounds in substantially the same relations. See also {{G3362}}, {{G3363}}, {{G3364}}, {{G3372}}, {{G3373}}, {{G3375}}, {{G3378}}.

3362.definition: [ἐὰν μή] i.e. {{G1437}} and {{G3361}}; if not, i.e. unless

3363.definition: [ἵνα μή] i.e. {{G2443}} and {{G3361}}; in order (or so) that not

3364.definition: [οὐ μή] i.e. {{G3756}} and {{G3361}}; a double negative strengthening the denial; not at all Compare {{G3378}}.

3365.definition: [μηδαμῶς] adverb from a compound of {{G3361}} and ἀμός (somebody); by no means

3366.definition: [μηδέ] from {{G3361}} and {{G1161}}; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor

3367.definition: [μηδείς] , including the irregular feminine      μηδεμία, and the neuter      μηδένfrom {{G3361}} and {{G1520}}; not even one (man, woman, thing)

3370.definition: [Μῆδος] of foreign origin (compare {{H4074}}); a Median, or inhabitant of Media

3372.definition: [μῆκος] probably akin to {{G3173}}; length (literally or figuratively) length.

3373.definition: [μηκύνω] from {{G3372}}; to lengthen, i.e. (middle voice) to enlarge

3375.definition: [μήν] a stronger form of {{G3303}}; a particle of affirmation (only with {{G2229}}); assuredly

3377.definition: [μηνύω] probably from the same base as {{G3145}} and {{G3415}} (i.e. μάω, to strive); to disclose (through the idea of mental effort and thus calling to mind), i.e. report, declare, intimate

3378.definition: [μὴ οὐκ]   may ook i.e. {{G3361}} and {{G3756}}; as interrogative and negative, is it not that? Compare {{G3364}}.

3379.definition: [μήποτε]  or       μή ποτεfrom {{G3361}} and {{G4218}}; not ever; also if (or lest) ever (or perhaps)

3381.definition: [μήπως]  or       μή πωςfrom {{G3361}} and {{G4458}}; lest somehow

3382.definition: [μηρός] perhaps a primary word; a thigh

3383.definition: [μήτε] from {{G3361}} and {{G5037}}; not too, i.e. (in continued negation) neither or nor; also, not even

3384.definition: [μήτηρ] apparently a primary word; a "mother" (literally or figuratively, immediate or remote)

3385.definition: [μήτι] from {{G3361}} and the neuter of {{G5100}}; whether at all

3386.definition: [μήτιγε] from {{G3385}} and {{G1065}}; not at all then, i.e. not to say (the rather still)

3387.definition: [μήτις]  or       μή τιςfrom {{G3361}} and {{G5100}}; whether any

3389.definition: [μητραλῴας] from {{G3384}} and the base of {{G257}}; a mother-thresher, i.e. matricide

3390.definition: [μητρόπολις] from {{G3384}} and {{G4172}}; a mother city, i.e. "metropolis"

3391.definition: [μία] irregular feminine of {{G1520}}; one or first

3392.definition: [μιαίνω] perhaps a primary verb; to sully or taint, i.e. contaminate (ceremonially or morally)

3397.definition: [μικρόν] masculine or neuter singular of {{G3398}} (as noun); a small space of time or degree

3398.definition: [μικρός] , including the comparative      μικρότεροςapparently a primary word; small (in size, quantity, number or (figuratively) dignity)

3399.definition: [Μίλητος] of uncertain origin; Miletus, a city of Asia Minor

3400.definition: [μίλιον] of Latin origin; a thousand paces, i.e. a "mile"
